cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.DC 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it explores different approaches to integrating a neural network with the Lucene search engine in a multi-stage ranking architecture. Additionally, the paper uses PyTorch, a deep learning toolkit, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research. The paper also evaluates the performance of the different integration approaches, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
